RYAN Gosling has paid tribute to a young Scots filmmaker by finally eating his cereal.
The movie star made a short Vine video of himself tucking into a bowl of cereal in memory of Ryan McHenry, the filmmaker who invented the &quot;Ryan Gosling won't eat his cereal&quot; meme .
Ryan who was from Dumfries and moved to Edinburgh when he was 18, passed away after a two-year battle against bone cancer.
In his tribute, the actor pours himself a bowl of cereal, before raising a spoon to McHenry's memory and munching his Corn Flakes.
  
Ryan also Tweeted in the early hours if this morning: &quot;My heart goes out to all of Ryan McHenry's family and friends. Feel very lucky to have been apart of his life in some small way.&quot;
 
My heart goes out to all of Ryan McHenry's family and friends. Feel very lucky to have been apart of his life in some small way.

Ryan McHenry first uploaded a six-second Vine showing Gosling appear to reject an offered spoonful of cereal in early 2013.
 

His videos went viral notching up millions of views online and even catching the attention of Gosling himself.
He discovered six months later that he was suffering from osteosarcoma bone cancer in his leg. Despite fundraising efforts to save him and news that he had beaten the disease last July the cancer returned and he died on Sunday.
